X:1
T:O Sacred Head, Now Wounded
C:Words: Bernard of Clairvaux, 1153. Tr. James W. Alexander, 1830.
C:Music: Passion Chorale, Hans Leo Hassler 1601; harmonized J.S. Bach 1729.
C:SSAATTBB arrangement for 8-part double choir and lever harp.
M:4/4
L:1/4
Q:1/4=80
%%staves [(V:1 V:2) (V:3 V:4) (V:5 V:6) (V:7 V:8)]
V:1 name="Soprano I"   clef=treble
V:2 name="Soprano II"  clef=treble
V:3 name="Alto I"      clef=treble
V:4 name="Alto II"     clef=treble
V:5 name="Tenor I"     clef=treble middle=B3 transpose=-12
V:6 name="Tenor II"    clef=treble middle=B3 transpose=-12
V:7 name="Baritone"    clef=bass
V:8 name="Bass I"      clef=bass
K:C
%% -----------------------------------------------------------
%% PHRASE A — first statement (reduced texture: S1 + TTBB)
%% SSAA inner voices rest. Dynamic: mp.
%% Chords: I IV I6 I / ii6 V I V / vi I vi V / vi
%% -----------------------------------------------------------
%%
%% Sounding pitches (concert):
%%  S1:  E4  | A4 G4 F4 E4  | D4(h) E4 B4  | C5 C5 B4/A4 B4 | A4(dh)
%%  T1:  G3  | F3 G3 A3 G3  | A3 G3 G3 G3  | A3 A3 A3 G3    | A3(dh)
%%  T2:  E3  | D3 E3 F3 E3  | F3 E3 E3 E3  | F3 F3 F3 E3    | F3(dh)
%%  Bar: C3  | A2 B2 C3 D3  | D3 C3 C3 B2  | C3 C3 C3 B2    | C3(dh)
%%  B1:  C2  | F2 E2 A2/B2  C2 | F2 G2 C2 B2 | A2/B2 C2/D2 E2 E2 | A2(dh)
%%
%% T written (treble, sounds 8va lower):
%%  T1 written: G | F G A G | (A G) G G | A A A G | A3
%%  T2 written: E | D E F E | (F E) E E | F F F E | F3
%%
%% Bar (bass clef, C=C3, B,=B2, A,=A2, D=D3, F,=F2, G,=G2, E,=E2, C,=C2):
%%  Bar: C | A, B, C D | (D C) C B, | C C C B, | C3
